@prefix : <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .

<> a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "RDF-to-HTML Infographic: Gated Workflow HowTo"@en ;
    schema:description "Full specification for the script-assisted, gate-first, port-don't-write protocol required for all RDF-backed HTML infographic generation. Recorded after session 2026-06-17 audit."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-06-17T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:dateModified "2026-06-17T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:about :howto .

:howto a schema:HowTo ;
    schema:name "RDF-to-HTML Infographic Gated Workflow"@en ;
    schema:description "Three-part enforcement protocol preventing the process failures observed in session 2026-06-17: unlinked entities, wrong predicate semantics, broken KG Explorer, and post-hoc validation."@en ;
    schema:step :step1, :step2, :step3 .

:step1 a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 1 ;
    schema:name "Script-Assisted Entity Extraction"@en ;
    schema:text """Before writing any HTML anchor:
1. Parse the companion TTL with rdflib into a Graph.
2. Extract structured entity map as JSON covering:
   - schema:DefinedTerm subjects → IRI, name, description, owl:sameAs
   - schema:Question subjects → IRI, name
   - schema:HowToStep subjects → IRI, name, position
   - schema:Person / schema:Organization subjects → IRI, name
   - schema:ArticleSection subjects → IRI, name
   - All other schema:name-bearing subjects → IRI, name, type
3. Use ONLY these extracted IRIs as href values. Never pattern-match from entity names.
4. Verify every DefinedTerm with a DBpedia/Wikidata match uses owl:sameAs (not rdfs:seeAlso) before generating HTML."""@en .

:step2 a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 2 ;
    schema:name "Gate-First Validator Protocol"@en ;
    schema:text """1. After HTML skeleton (structure only): run validate-harness-contract.py. Fix all failures before adding content.
2. After each major section (KG Explorer, glossary, FAQ, HowTo, SPARQL workbench): run validator again. Fix before next section.
3. PASS required before any output is shown to user. Never deliver a known-failing artifact.
Command:
  python3 .../rdf-infographic-skill/scripts/validate-harness-contract.py \\
    /path/{stem}.html --ttl /path/{stem}.ttl"""@en .

:step3 a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 3 ;
    schema:name "Port KG Explorer — Never Write From Scratch"@en ;
    schema:text """1. List the HTML output folder; grep for d3.forceSimulation or updateGraph to find a validated prior artifact.
2. Copy initKG() + updateGraph() + predIriMap + nid() + getFilteredData() + applyFilters() verbatim from that artifact.
3. Parameterise only: article base IRI (predIriMap fallback), predIriMap entries (from TTL predicates), kgCore/kgFull payloads (from TTL).
4. Never rewrite D3 drag, zoom, simulation, or layer management from scratch."""@en .

:rationale a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "Why this rule exists"@en ;
    schema:description "Session 2026-06-17 audit of public-trust-problem-ai-claude_sonnet_4_6-1 artifacts found: HTML authored in parallel with TTL (not derived from it); validator run post-delivery; KG Explorer written from scratch causing SVG drag conflict and broken resolver links. Resulted in 13 unlinked entities, 2 missing glossary terms, rdfs:seeAlso instead of owl:sameAs on 5 DefinedTerms, missing JSON-LD companion, and broken KG node/edge hyperlinks."@en .
